- Use `@Transactional` annotation to mark Redis transactional methods.
- Ensure Spring Data Redis version is up-to-date, e.g., `2.6.4.RELEASE`.
- Configure Redis connection properties in `application.properties` or `application.yml`.
- Utilize `RedisTemplate` for executing commands within transactions.
- Example of a transaction method:
  ```java
  @Transactional
  public void performTransaction() {
      redisTemplate.multi();
      try {
          redisTemplate.opsForValue().increment("counter");
          redisTemplate.opsForSet().add("setKey", "value");
      } catch (Exception e) {
          redisTemplate.discard();
          throw e;
      }
      redisTemplate.exec();
  }
  ```
- Key config options in `application.properties`:
  ```properties
  spring.redis.host=localhost
  spring.redis.port=6379
  spring.redis.password=
  ```
- Use `redis-cli --version` to check the latest Redis CLI version.
- For debugging, enable transaction logging by setting `spring.data.redis.debug-level=TRACE`.
